{
  "texts": [
    "(2 × win + tie) / (number of prompts)×100.",
    "If needed, we indirectly compare the models based on their performance against the chosen responses.",
    "Noisy labels are prevalent in preference datasets often arising from vague annotation criteria and ambivalent data that induce conflicting preferences, making it difficult for annotators to articulate their choices.",
    "In some cases, paired responses differ only slightly or are nearly identical (Figure 2), which may not provide a clear basis for the model to learn meaningful preferences.",
    "GPT-4 as a judge exhibits similar patterns to human annotators (Bubeck et al., 2023), facing the same issues (Figure 3)."
  ]
}